### 4.3 LangGraph State — What Gets Passed Between Agents

All agents share a single Python `TypedDict` object. Each agent reads what it needs and writes its output back to this shared state:

```python
# The shared state passed through the entire LangGraph pipeline
class AlertState(TypedDict):
    # Set by the ingestion layer
    alert_id:         str          # Unique identifier
    raw_payload:      str          # Raw log text (UNTRUSTED)
    source_ip:        str
    event_type:       str

    # Set by Guardrail Agent
    is_clean:         bool         # False if injection detected
    injection_reason: str

    # Set by Triage Agent
    severity:         str          # P1, P2, P3, or P4
    mitre_tactic:     str          # e.g. 'Lateral Movement'
    mitre_technique:  str          # e.g. 'T1021.001'
    confidence:       float        # 0.0 to 1.0
    triage_rationale: str

    # Set by Context Agent
    retrieved_techniques: list     # Top-3 from ChromaDB

    # Set by Investigator Agent
    incident_summary:    str       # Human-readable report
    recommended_actions: list      # 3 remediation steps
```

